Given a 2D array (matrix), the task is to count the total number of even numbers and odd numbers present in the matrix.

Input Format

The first line contains the size of the matrix N (number of rows and columns)

The next N lines contain M integers each, representing the matrix.

Constraints

NA

Output Format

The output prints two integers separated by a space:

The first integer represents the count of even numbers.

The second integer represents the count of odd numbers.

Sample Input 0

3
1 2 3
4 5 6
7 8 9
Sample Output 0

4 5
Explanation 0

Even numbers = {2,4,6,8} → 4 Odd numbers = {1,3,5,7,9} → 5


import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int arr[][]=new int[n][n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                arr[i][j]=sc.nextInt();
            }
        }
        int e=0;
        int o=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                if(arr[i][j]%2==0)
                {
                    e++;
                }
                else if(arr[i][j]!=0)
                {
                    o++;
                }
            }
        }
        System.out.print(e+" "+o);
    }
}
